Program: The Reith Lectures
Title: Eliza Manningham-Buller: Terror
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0145x77
Last Broadcast Date: Sat 10 Sep 2011
The former Director-General of the Security Service (MI5), Eliza Manningham-Buller gives the first of her BBC Reith Lectures 2011 called " Terror." On the tenth anniversary of the attacks on the United States on September 11th she reflects on the lasting significance of that day. Was it a "terrorist" crime, an act of war or something different? Show less